To check how to use those dockerfiles, please see the readme in that folder:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/docker/README.md

The link you are seeing there should not exist. its version string is 0.0.0

Those dockerfiles cannot be used without the parameterized_docker_build.sh script.
For the newer and more flexible dockerfiles, please see https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/dockerfiles

body:
To check how to use those dockerfiles, please see the readme in that folder:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/docker/README.md

The link you are seeing there should not exist. its version string is `0.0.0`

Those dockerfiles **cannot** be used without the `parameterized_docker_build.sh` script.
For the newer and more flexible dockerfiles, please see https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/dockerfiles
